@SBK in TO Both the π and the τ as in πτηνά (birds) and πτέρυγα (wing) are pronounced. 

As do the p of ‘pn’ in pneumonia (πνευμονία) and the n  of ‘mn’ in mnemonic (μνημονικό) no matter what recent cluing in the NYT puzzle may lead you to believe 😀😀

Greek pronunciation of diphthongs αι ευ ει οι αυ and double consonants μπ (today’s OLYMPIAD) but sometimes (depending on placement) making the sound ‘b’ , γγ for ‘g’, γκ for a different ‘g’, ντ for ‘d’ can be confusing.

