@Marie

Some modern games are still pretty great though. In recent years I enjoyed the less-than-well critically received Star Wars: Outlaws, for example, and the superb Polish dark fantasy Tainted Grail: The Fall of Avalon.

But yeah, I yearn for something as immersive as, say, Knights of the Old Republic. When I first played that game, I let my character succumb to the dark side of the force, simply because it made gameplay easier, especially in the beginning. And then it turned out that had some horrific, narrative consequences. What I had to do as a Sith still haunts me over 20 years later... In fact, the experience was so formative, it was the last time I roleplayed as a villain, ever.

