@Andrzej 

Probably they want to motivate you to install the app, because the app generates trackers. The NYT apps...the one for gsmes, the one for food, and the main one... generate hundreds of trackers per day, and the information gathered by those is a valuable commodity.

I have other apps on my phone that generate trackers, but none of them do so on the scale of the NYT apps.

@Andrzej 

I use an Android phone, along with the Games app, and everything, including the comments, seems to be functional.

I do have some pretty aggrassive privacy software, including some provisions against app trackers, but no doubt it would all be useless if I truly attracted the wrong sort of attention.

