I can’t find a discussion of MODE below. I can’t help wondering what the problem is. There is no technical definition in statistics for the word AVERAGE. It’s a nontechnical way to talk about typical values in a set of data.  The MODE is one of 3 ways that are generally used for that purpose, depending on the data and how the result is used.
Check the definition of AVERAGE in Merriam Webster Dictionary, for example.

